episodes.title: Homer's Barbershop Quartet
episodes.plot: After the kids find a record with Homer's picture on it, he recalls the story of how he achieved fame in the 1980s with his barbershop quartet, The Be Sharps.

episodes.title: Cape Feare
episodes.plot: After being released from prison on parole, Sideshow Bob plots to murder Bart.

episodes.title: Homer Goes to College
episodes.plot: When a surprise inspection of the nuclear power plant reveals that Homer is not qualified to do his job, he is forced to go to college.

episodes.title: Rosebud
episodes.plot: After his birthday party goes wrong, Mr. Burns begins to want his childhood toy, a teddy bear named Bobo; Homer finds that Maggie is in possession of the doll.

episodes.title: Treehouse of Horror IV
episodes.plot: Homer sells his soul to the Devil for a donut, Bart contends with a gremlin on the side of the school bus which only he can see, and the family discovers that Mr. Burns is a vampire.

episodes.title: Marge on the Lam
episodes.plot: A girls' night out turns into a high speed chase when Marge learns her friend is driving a stolen car.

episodes.title: Bart's Inner Child
episodes.plot: Brad Goodman, a self-help guru, encourages Springfield to act more like Bart, with disastrous results.

episodes.title: Boy Scoutz 'n the Hood
episodes.plot: After joining the Junior Campers while on a sugar high, Bart reluctantly invites Homer to accompany him on the group's annual father-son rafting trip, which soon goes awry.

episodes.title: The Last Temptation of Homer
episodes.plot: Homer's marriage is in trouble when he develops an attraction to a new co-worker; Bart undergoes medical treatments that make him look like a nerd.

episodes.title: $pringfield (Or, How I Learned to Stop Worrying and Love Legalized Gambling)
episodes.plot: Mr. Burns builds a casino when Springfield decides to legalize gambling, with Marge becoming addicted to the slot machines.

episodes.title: Homer the Vigilante
episodes.plot: An outbreak of burglaries inspires Homer to lead a vigilante group.

episodes.title: Bart Gets Famous
episodes.plot: Bart becomes an overnight sensation as the "I didn't do it" boy on Krusty the Clown's show.

episodes.title: Homer and Apu
episodes.plot: Apu moves in with the Simpsons after losing his job when Homer gets ill from the contaminated food; James Woods takes over the Kwik-E-Mart.

episodes.title: Lisa vs. Malibu Stacy
episodes.plot: Angered by the vacuous phrases her Malibu Stacy doll utters, Lisa works with Malibu Stacy's original designer to create a doll with admirable traits.

episodes.title: Deep Space Homer
episodes.plot: In an effort to increase the dismal television ratings for their space launches, NASA decides to send an ordinary man into space, and Homer is chosen for the task.

episodes.title: Homer Loves Flanders
episodes.plot: After Flanders invites Homer to a football game, the pair become friends, but Homer's possessiveness and loutish behaviour slowly turns Ned against him.

episodes.title: Bart Gets an Elephant
episodes.plot: After Bart receives an elephant as a prize for calling in to a radio station, the animal proves to be too costly to care for and Homer decides to sell it.

episodes.title: Burns' Heir
episodes.plot: After coming close to death, Mr. Burns decides than it's time to find an heir to his empire, and chooses Bart because of his truly devious nature.

episodes.title: Sweet Seymour Skinner's Baadasssss Song
episodes.plot: Bart accidentally gets Principal Skinner fired on inspection day, with Ned Flanders taking over as his replacement.

episodes.title: The Boy Who Knew Too Much
episodes.plot: Bart witnesses the alleged assault of a waiter by Mayor Quimby's nephew, but coming forward will mean admitting to skipping class, and face the consequences.

episodes.title: Lady Bouvier's Lover
episodes.plot: Grampa falls in love with Marge's mother, but must compete with Mr. Burns for her heart.

episodes.title: Secrets of a Successful Marriage
episodes.plot: Homer begins teaching a class on how to have a successful marriage, but jeopardizes his own marriage by revealing secrets about himself and Marge.
